<h2 id="add-CNAME-file-to-github"><strong>4. Add CNAME File to Github Pages.</strong></h2>

<p>In order to add <strong>CNAME</strong>, click on the upload/New file located at the top right corner of the repository page. Save the file name as <strong>CNAME</strong> with your personal <strong>domain name</strong> in it.</p>

<p>Importantly, we need to save the file name as <strong>CNAME</strong> by including our personal <strong>Godaddy domain name</strong> in it. After filling all the required field hit the commit button with a commit message.</p>

<p>In my case, I filled my <strong>CNAME</strong> file as shown in the image below.</p>

<figure>
<img src="/uploads/adding-CNAME-file.png" data-src="/uploads/adding-CNAME-file.png" class="lazy" alt="adding-CNAME-file" title="adding-CNAME-file" />
<figcaption>Adding CNAME File To Github</figcaption>
</figure>

