<h2 id="configure-DNS-server-for-domain-name"><strong>5. Configure DNS Server For DOMAIN Name.</strong></h2>

<p>Over at <a href="https://in.godaddy.com/" target="\_blank" rel="noopener">https://in.godaddy.com/</a> head to the ‚Äú<strong>Manage DNS</strong>‚Äù tab and scroll to the ‚Äú<strong>Custom resource records</strong>‚Äù section at the bottom of the page.</p>

<ol>
<li> We need to <strong>add</strong> two "<strong>@</strong>" type <strong>A records</strong> that point to the <strong>Github IP's 192.30.252.153</strong> and <strong>192.30.252.154</strong>. </li>
<li> We also need to add one "<strong>www</strong>" <strong>CNAME record</strong> that points to your <strong>USERNAME.github.io</strong> URL. </li>
</ol>

<p>In my case, I added the following records at <strong>GoDaddy registrar</strong> as shown in the following image below.</p>

<figure>
<img src="/uploads/setting-DNS-records.png" data-src="/uploads/setting-DNS-records.png" class="lazy" alt="setting-DNS-records" title="setting-DNS-records" />
<figcaption>Setting DNS Records</figcaption>
</figure>

<p>After completing all the steps, we can really check the <strong>live status</strong> of our website with a <strong>custom URL</strong> which directly redirects our <strong>username.github.io</strong> URL to our <strong>personal domain URL</strong>.</p>

